---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical} og={og} schema={schema} active={active}>
<!-- ═══ PAGE HEADER ═══ -->
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Pest Control in Vernal, Utah</h1>
    <p>Your local, family-owned pest control team — based right here in the Uintah Basin since 1994.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ AI SUMMARY BLOCK (Layer 1) ═══ -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-bottom:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="reveal" style="max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; background: var(--gray-light, #f5f5f5); border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px 28px;">
        <p style="margin:0; color: var(--dark, #1a1a1a); line-height: 1.7;"><strong>Wernex Termite &amp; Pest Control</strong> is Vernal's hometown pest control company — headquartered at 6097 Dry Fork Canyon Rd and serving the Uintah Basin since 1994. We protect homes, businesses, ranches, and rentals across Vernal, Naples, Maeser, Ballard, Jensen, and all of Uintah County from rodents, spiders, ants, wasps, box elder bugs, and seasonal invaders. Services include free inspections, targeted treatments, rodent exclusion, and year-round prevention plans. Licensed, insured, and locally owned. <a href="tel:+14356739503">Call (435) 673-9503</a> for a free quote.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ WHY VERNAL / LOCAL ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="reveal">
          <span class="section-label">Locally Owned</span>
          <h2>Vernal's Hometown Pest Control Company</h2>
          <p style="margin: 16px 0; color: var(--gray);">When you call Wernex, you reach a company that is actually here in Vernal — not a national franchise routing your call to a call center hundreds of miles away. Our office sits on Dry Fork Canyon Road, our technicians live in the Uintah Basin, and we have been protecting local homes and businesses since 1994. That means when you have a pest problem, you get a fast response from people who know the area, know the pests, and stand behind their work.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">Vernal's location and climate create a pest profile all its own. Sitting at roughly 5,300 feet in the high desert of northeastern Utah, the Uintah Basin swings from hot, dry summers to genuinely cold winters. Those long winters don't get rid of pests — they push mice, spiders, box elder bugs, and cluster flies indoors looking for warmth. The surrounding ranch land, irrigated fields, and energy-sector activity mean rural properties, outbuildings, and shops all see their own pressures.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">We're also proud to serve a community that lives close to the outdoors. With Dinosaur National Monument, Flaming Gorge, the Ashley National Forest, and the Green River all on our doorstep, Basin homeowners spend a lot of time outside — and the last thing anyone wants is to bring the bugs back home. Our job is to keep the line between the desert and your living room firmly in place, all year long.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal">
          <img src="images/14.webp" alt="Wernex Termite & Pest Control team standing in front of a branded service truck in Vernal, Utah" style="width:100%; height:100%; min-height:340px; object-fit:cover; border-radius:16px; box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,.18);" loading="lazy">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ COMMON PESTS ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Know Your Pests</span>
        <h2>Common Pests in Vernal &amp; the Uintah Basin</h2>
        <p class="mx-auto" style="margin-top:12px;color:var(--gray);">The Basin's high-desert climate and rural surroundings bring a predictable set of seasonal invaders. Here are the ones we treat most.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="service-cards" style="margin-top: 40px;">
        <a href="rodent-control-vernal.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--green">🐭</div>
          <h3>Mice &amp; Rodents</h3>
          <p>Deer mice and voles are our number-one cold-weather call. They slip into homes, garages, barns, and outbuildings through gaps the width of a pencil. We trap, exclude, and seal entry points — see our dedicated <a href="rodent-control-vernal.html">Vernal rodent control</a> page.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--amber">🕷️</div>
          <h3>Spiders</h3>
          <p>From harmless cellar and wolf spiders to the occasional black widow in garages and woodpiles, spiders are a year-round nuisance in the Basin. We remove webs and egg sacs and treat the harborage areas where they hide.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--green">🐜</div>
          <h3>Ants</h3>
          <p>Ants forage indoors for food and moisture, especially in kitchens. We target the colony — not just the trail — so the problem doesn't simply come back a week later.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--amber">🐝</div>
          <h3>Wasps &amp; Hornets</h3>
          <p>Paper wasps and hornets build nests under eaves, in sheds, and around play areas through the summer. We remove nests safely and treat to discourage them from rebuilding.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--green">🪲</div>
          <h3>Box Elder Bugs</h3>
          <p>Each fall, box elder bugs swarm sunny south- and west-facing walls and work their way inside to overwinter. Exterior treatment timed to the season keeps them out before they get in.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="service-card reveal">
          <div class="service-card__icon service-card__icon--amber">🪰</div>
          <h3>Cluster Flies &amp; Others</h3>
          <p>Cluster flies, earwigs, silverfish, and other occasional invaders show up with the seasons. A prevention plan handles them as part of routine service instead of one emergency at a time.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ OUR APPROACH ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="reveal">
          <img src="images/30.webp" alt="Wernex technician sealing roof-line entry points to exclude rodents and pests from a Vernal Utah home" style="width:100%; height:100%; min-height:300px; object-fit:cover; border-radius:16px; box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,.18);" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="reveal">
          <span class="section-label">Our Approach</span>
          <h2>How Wernex Protects Your Property</h2>
          <p style="margin: 16px 0; color: var(--gray);">Good pest control is more than spraying a baseboard. We use an integrated approach that finds the source of the problem, removes it, and then keeps it from coming back — so you spend less over time and deal with fewer surprises.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);"><strong>Inspect &amp; identify.</strong> Every job starts with a walk-through of your property. We pinpoint where pests are getting in, where they're nesting, and what's drawing them — moisture, food, clutter, or gaps in the structure.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);"><strong>Treat &amp; exclude.</strong> We apply targeted treatments where pests actually live and travel, and we seal the entry points that let them in. For rodents in particular, exclusion — closing up those pencil-width gaps — is what keeps them out for good.</p>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);"><strong>Prevent year-round.</strong> Because Basin pests move with the seasons, our prevention plans time service to the calendar: barrier treatments before the fall rodent and box elder push, and follow-ups in spring as activity rebuilds. If something shows up between visits, we come back. <a href="contact.html">Get a free quote</a> to get started.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ SEASONAL CALENDAR ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Year in the Basin</span>
        <h2>The Uintah Basin Pest Calendar</h2>
        <p class="mx-auto" style="margin-top:12px;color:var(--gray);max-width:740px;">Pest pressure in Vernal follows the seasons closely. Knowing what's coming helps you stay ahead of it — and shapes how we time our prevention plans.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cards-grid" style="margin-top: 40px; max-width: 1000px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>🌱 Spring</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">As the snow melts and the ground warms, ants become active and start foraging indoors, and overwintering spiders and box elder bugs that sheltered in walls begin moving around. Spring is the time to knock back populations before they build through summer.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>☀️ Summer</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">Hot Basin summers bring peak wasp and hornet activity around eaves, sheds, and play areas, along with ants and spiders at their busiest. Outdoor living means more contact with stinging insects — this is the season for nest removal and exterior barriers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>🍂 Fall</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">The most important season of all. As nights cool, mice, voles, box elder bugs, and cluster flies all push toward the warmth of your home. Timing exclusion and exterior treatment now — before the first hard freeze — is what keeps them out all winter.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card reveal">
          <div class="card__body">
            <h3>❄️ Winter</h3>
            <p style="color:var(--gray);">Cold weather doesn't stop indoor problems — rodents that got in during fall keep breeding in attics and walls, and overwintering insects emerge on warm days. Interior service and monitoring catch these before spring kicks off the cycle again.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ TESTIMONIAL ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Customer Reviews</span>
        <h2>What Uintah Basin Residents Say</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="testimonial-grid" style="margin-top: 40px;">
        <div class="testimonial reveal">
          <div class="testimonial__stars">★★★★★</div>
          <p class="testimonial__text">"Friendly &amp; efficient! Helped me when I had a huge ant problem when my old company wouldn't even call me back! Wernex is my go to pest control company!"</p>
          <div class="testimonial__author">
            <div class="testimonial__avatar">JT</div>
            <div>
              <div class="testimonial__name">Jeannie Turpin</div>
              <div class="testimonial__loc">Verified Google Review</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="testimonial reveal">
          <div class="testimonial__stars">★★★★★</div>
          <p class="testimonial__text">"I love the staff at Wernex &amp; the friendly prompt service. I love the price. I have used them for years &amp; have been very satisfied. They are great."</p>
          <div class="testimonial__author">
            <div class="testimonial__avatar">JB</div>
            <div>
              <div class="testimonial__name">Judy Bell</div>
              <div class="testimonial__loc">Verified Google Review</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: 36px;">
        <a href="testimonials.html" class="btn btn--lime">Read All Reviews →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ FAQ SECTION (Layer 2 — Structured Q&A) ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Common Questions</span>
        <h2>Pest Control FAQs — Vernal</h2>
      </div>
      <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 36px auto 0;">

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light); padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Is Wernex actually based in Vernal?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">Yes. Wernex Termite &amp; Pest Control is headquartered in Vernal at 6097 Dry Fork Canyon Rd — we are not a national franchise routing calls through a distant office. We have served the Uintah Basin since 1994, our technicians live and work here, and those local roots mean faster response times and real familiarity with the pests that affect Vernal homes and businesses.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light); padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">What pests are most common in Vernal and the Uintah Basin?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">The most common calls we get in Vernal are for rodents (deer mice and voles, especially as the weather cools), spiders, ants, wasps and hornets in summer, and box elder bugs and cluster flies that gather on sunny walls in fall. Rural and ranch properties also deal with mice in outbuildings and barns. Our prevention plans are built around this seasonal cycle.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light); padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Do I really need year-round pest control with Vernal's cold winters?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">Yes. Cold winters don't eliminate pests — they drive them indoors. Mice, spiders, box elder bugs, and cluster flies all seek the warmth of your home as temperatures drop, and many overwinter inside walls and attics. A year-round plan seals entry points before the fall push and keeps populations from rebuilding in spring, which is far more effective than treating one problem at a time.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-light); padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">What areas around Vernal does Wernex serve?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">From our Vernal base we serve all of Uintah County and the wider Uintah Basin, including Naples, Maeser, Ballard, Jensen, Lapoint, Roosevelt, Duchesne, and the surrounding rural and ranch communities. If you're not sure whether you're in our area, just call <a href="tel:+14356739503">(435) 673-9503</a> and we'll let you know.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item reveal" style="padding: 24px 0;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 8px;">How much does pest control cost in Vernal?</h3>
          <p style="color: var(--gray);">Cost depends on the size of your property, the pests involved, and whether you choose a one-time treatment or an ongoing prevention plan. Wernex provides free, no-obligation quotes for Vernal homeowners and businesses. <a href="contact.html">Contact us</a> or call <a href="tel:+14356739503">(435) 673-9503</a> and we'll give you straightforward pricing with no pressure.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ CTA BANNER ═══ -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-banner reveal">
        <div>
          <h2>Dealing With Pests in Vernal?</h2>
          <p>Free quotes. Fast local response. No obligation. 4.5★ rated on Google.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cta-banner__buttons">
          <a href="contact.html" class="btn btn--primary">Get a Free Quote →</a>
          <a href="tel:+14356739503" class="btn btn--white">📞 (435) 673-9503</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ AREAS SERVED ═══ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Service Area</span>
        <h2>Pest Control Across the Uintah Basin</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="areas-grid" style="margin-top: 36px;">
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Vernal</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Naples</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Maeser</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Ballard</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Jensen</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Lapoint</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Roosevelt</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Duchesne</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Tridell</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Whiterocks</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Uintah County</a>
        <a href="contact.html" class="reveal">Duchesne County</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ RELATED PEST CONTROL SERVICES (Internal linking hub §4.2) ═══ -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top:40px; padding-bottom:40px; background:var(--gray-light, #f5f5f5);">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 880px;">
      <div class="text-center reveal" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
        <span class="section-label">Related Services</span>
        <h3 style="margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 0;">More From Wernex</h3>
      </div>
      <ul style="list-style:none; padding:0; margin:0; display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; justify-content:center; gap:12px 28px;">
        <li><a href="rodent-control-vernal.html">Rodent Control in Vernal</a></li>
        <li><a href="services.html">Full Service List</a></li>
        <li><a href="pest-library.html">Pest Library</a></li>
        <li><a href="contact.html">Schedule an Appointment</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══ FOOTER ═══ -->
</BaseLayout>
